From: burakgon <burakgon12@gmail.com>
Subject: [PATCH] ASoC: Intel: sof_sdw: Add SOC_SDW_SIDECAR_AMPS quirk for ASUS ExpertBook Ultra B9406CAA

The 2026 ASUS ExpertBook Ultra (B9406CAA, Panther Lake) ships the same
SoundWire codec topology that Dell SKU 0DD6 already has a quirk for: a
Cirrus CS42L43 headset/codec on link 3 plus two CS35L56 sidecar speaker
amplifiers on link 2 (PCI subsystem 0x1043:0x15e4).

Without SOC_SDW_SIDECAR_AMPS the topology blob is selected correctly
(sof-ptl-cs42l43-agg-l3-cs35l56-l2.tplg loads), and once the OEM-specific
firmware blobs land in linux-firmware (cs35l56-b0-dsp1-misc-104315e4-l2u{0,1}.{wmfw,bin})
the amps engage, but ALSA UCM cannot match the resulting card to a HiFi
profile because no sof_sdw quirk flag was set for it. WirePlumber falls
back to "stereo-fallback" and the speaker sink never reaches the cs35l56
output path. End-user symptom: speakers silent through PipeWire even when
direct ALSA playback to plughw:0,2 produces sound.

Mirror the existing Dell PTL+CS42L43 quirk; the only change is the DMI
match. SOC_SDW_SIDECAR_AMPS is the correct flag for this exact codec
topology.

Tested on ASUS ExpertBook Ultra B9406CAA, Linux 7.x.

Signed-off-by: burakgon <burakgon12@gmail.com>
---
 sound/soc/intel/boards/sof_sdw.c | 8 ++++++++
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+)

diff --git a/sound/soc/intel/boards/sof_sdw.c b/sound/soc/intel/boards/sof_sdw.c
--- a/sound/soc/intel/boards/sof_sdw.c
+++ b/sound/soc/intel/boards/sof_sdw.c
@@ -780,6 +780,14 @@ static const struct dmi_system_id sof_sdw_quirk_table[] = {
 		},
 		.driver_data = (void *)(SOC_SDW_SIDECAR_AMPS),
 	},
+	{
+		.callback = sof_sdw_quirk_cb,
+		.matches = {
+			DMI_MATCH(DMI_SYS_VENDOR, "ASUS"),
+			DMI_EXACT_MATCH(DMI_PRODUCT_NAME, "ASUS EXPERTBOOK B9406CAA")
+		},
+		.driver_data = (void *)(SOC_SDW_SIDECAR_AMPS),
+	},
 	{
 		.callback = sof_sdw_quirk_cb,
 		.matches = {
--
